<task id="024" project="sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair">
  <metadata>
    <title>P1.E1 — Spe.Integration.Tests classify failures (FR-13)</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>1.5-2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent</assigned>
    <tags>phase-1, integration-triage, bff-api, testing, p1-e</tags>
    <parallel-group>1-A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Read-only against `baseline/integration-test-baseline-*.trx`; writes only to `projects/.../integration-test-triage.md`; disjoint from all sibling Wave 1-A tasks (010, 011, 012, 013, 015, 017, 020, 021, 022)</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Classify the `Spe.Integration.Tests` failures from the Phase 0 baseline TRX into the design.md
    §6.2 triage taxonomy. Per FR-13 the classification must distinguish:
      - **compile drift** — file does not compile (signature change against current production)
      - **signature drift** — file compiles but uses a deprecated/changed API at runtime
      - **real Graph regression** — production calls Microsoft Graph differently; either Graph
        changed or production changed; needs verification before Phase 2+3 plan
      - **wiremock drift** — WireMock fixture no longer matches the request shape production sends

    Classification informs Phase 2+3 P23.I task scope. Each classified failure links to a
    target P23.I sub-task in the resulting triage document.

    READ-ONLY against `baseline/`. NO code changes. NO production changes. Output is the
    structured triage document only.
  </prompt>

  <role>AI agent classifying integration test failures into a taxonomy that drives Phase 2+3 planning.</role>

  <goal>
    `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/integration-test-triage.md` exists with: (a) total
    Spe.Integration.Tests failure count from Phase 0 baseline, (b) per-failure classification
    (compile drift / signature drift / real Graph regression / wiremock drift), (c) suggested
    fix scope per failure, (d) dependency on Phase 1 helpers (e.g., P1.B AsyncEnumerable helper
    if applicable), (e) target Phase 2+3 P23.I sub-task per failure.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="baseline">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/integration-test-baseline-2026-MM-DD.trx</file>
    <file purpose="integration-project">tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">No source/production code modifications; classification only</constraint>
    <constraint source="FR-13">Each failure has a classification from the 4-category taxonomy</constraint>
    <constraint source="§5.3">Spe.Integration.Tests are IN SCOPE; Phase 2+3 P23.I absorbs the repair work</constraint>
    <constraint source="§6.2">Use the project's triage taxonomy; final end-states `repaired` / `real-bug-pending-fix` / `flaky-quarantined` / archived</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-007-spefilestore.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per design.md §5.3 the Spe.Integration.Tests project is in scope (Option A "robust over
      easy") because integration tests catch real Graph/SPE behavior unit tests cannot. The
      2026-05-29 BFF audit identified Graph drift as a recurring incident source. Per §7 P1.E,
      Phase 1 produces the baseline + classified failure list; Phase 2+3 P23.I executes the
      repair. This task is the classification half of P1.E (Phase 0 task 002 captured the
      baseline TRX).
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="002" status="not-started">Integration test baseline TRX captured in Phase 0</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/integration-test-triage.md</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/integration-test-baseline-2026-MM-DD.trx`. Parse `&lt;UnitTestResult outcome="Failed"&gt;` entries.</step>
    <step order="2">For each failure, capture: test name, stack trace head, error message. Inspect the corresponding source file under `tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/` to confirm classification context.</step>
    <step order="3">Classify each failure into ONE of the 4 categories:
      - `compile-drift` — error references missing namespace/type/method that exists in newer production signature
      - `signature-drift` — runtime API mismatch (e.g., `MissingMethodException` at execution)
      - `graph-regression` — Microsoft Graph SDK call shape changed OR production now sends a different request shape; needs deeper investigation
      - `wiremock-drift` — WireMock stub no longer matches request (request path / headers / body assertion fails)</step>
    <step order="4">For each failure, suggest a fix-scope size: `S` (single-file mechanical), `M` (cross-file signature update + WireMock update), `L` (likely production-bug suspicion needs investigation; flag for `real-bug-pending-fix`).</step>
    <step order="5">Identify Phase 1 helper dependencies: e.g., if a failure uses `IAsyncEnumerable&lt;T&gt;`, flag P1.B helper as prerequisite for repair.</step>
    <step order="6">Map each failure to a target Phase 2+3 P23.I sub-task (group similar failures together for batching efficiency).</step>
    <step order="7">Write `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/integration-test-triage.md` with sections:
      - `## Summary` — total Spe.Integration.Tests failures, per-category counts
      - `## Per-failure classification` — table: Test name | Category | Suggested fix scope (S/M/L) | Phase 1 helper dependency | Target P23.I sub-task ID
      - `## Real-bug suspicions` — failures classified `graph-regression` warranting `real-bug-pending-fix` triage in Phase 2+3
      - `## Phase 2+3 input` — bulleted handoff to P23.I task generation</step>
    <step order="8">Update `current-task.md` declaring P1.E Track exit gate.</step>
    <step order="9">Verify `git status` shows ONLY `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/integration-test-triage.md` as new file.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="git">status</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/integration-test-triage.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`integration-test-triage.md` exists with all 4 named sections</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Per-failure classification table has 1 row per Spe.Integration.Tests failure from baseline TRX</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Each failure assigned to ONE of the 4 categories</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Each failure has fix-scope size (S/M/L)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Each failure mapped to a target P23.I sub-task ID</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No modifications to `src/`, `tests/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">P1.E Track exit gate declared in `current-task.md`</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
